  <prompt>
    Run the final audit of `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/` to confirm zero email-touching duplicate forks of `@spaarke/ui-components` remain. Per FR-25, after Waves 3–5 migrations, every email-touching component in LegalWorkspace should either (a) be a thin re-export from `@spaarke/ui-components`, or (b) be a LegalWorkspace-specific component with no shared-lib counterpart.

    Per CLAUDE.md empirical finding #9, the project's only confirmed true fork was `CreateMatter/SendEmailStep.tsx` (deleted in Wave 5 task 074). This audit verifies that finding holds AND nothing was introduced between then and now.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    React component architecture specialist familiar with the LegalWorkspace solution structure and the canonical `@spaarke/ui-components` shared lib. Authoritative on the empirical fork inventory from project pre-flight.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A final audit document at `notes/research/084-final-fork-audit.md` confirming zero email-touching forks remain in LegalWorkspace. The audit document is the binding evidence for the FR-25 acceptance criterion. Any fork found is filed as a remediation task and resolved before Wave 6 completes.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      LegalWorkspace historically forked shared-lib components for various reasons. R3 spec FR-25 mandates that all email-touching forks (CreateMatter/CreateProject/CreateEvent/CreateTodo/CreateWorkAssignment/SummarizeFiles/FilePreview) be removed in favor of re-exports from `@spaarke/ui-components`.

      Per empirical CLAUDE.md finding #9: only `CreateMatter/SendEmailStep.tsx` was a true fork. Project/Event/Todo/WorkAssignment dirs exist in LegalWorkspace but contain NO email-touching SendEmailStep — they were never forked. SummarizeFiles fork was deleted in Wave 4. FilePreview was migrated to use the canonical SendEmailDialog wrapper in Wave 3 (no fork to delete).

      This task verifies the final state.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/CreateMatter/</file>
