  <steps>
    <step order="1">Enumerate every file under `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/{CreateMatter,CreateProject,CreateEvent,CreateTodo,CreateWorkAssignment,SummarizeFiles,FilePreview}/`. List file paths.</step>
    <step order="2">For each file, classify it: (a) thin re-export from `@spaarke/ui-components` (one-liner `export *` or named re-export), (b) LegalWorkspace-specific component with no shared-lib counterpart (legitimate), (c) email-touching fork (FAIL — must be remediated).</step>
    <step order="3">Grep for inline `fetch` calls to `/api/communications/send` in LegalWorkspace: `grep -r "fetch.*communications/send" src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/`. Expect ZERO hits.</step>
    <step order="4">Grep for direct imports of `sendCommunication` from anywhere other than `@spaarke/ui-components`: `grep -r "import.*sendCommunication" src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/`. Expect all hits to be from `@spaarke/ui-components`.</step>
    <step order="5">Grep for cross-package source-path imports (the WorkAssignment dialog antipattern): `grep -rn "from '\.\./\.\./\.\./\.\./shared/" src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/`. Expect zero such patterns referencing email-related paths.</step>
    <step order="6">Verify `WorkAssignmentWizardDialog.tsx:31` now imports from `@spaarke/ui-components` (was resolved in Wave 5 task 073).</step>
    <step order="7">Document the audit in `notes/research/084-final-fork-audit.md` with: classification table per file, grep results, verdict (✅ zero forks confirmed / ⚠ forks found requiring remediation).</step>
    <step order="8">If forks found: file remediation tasks and STOP. If clean: proceed.</step>
    <step order="9">Cross-link the audit document from Wave 6 PR description.</step>
    <step order="10">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 084 ✅ completed.</step>
    <step order="11">Update `current-task.md`: status → completed, advance.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="grep">Empirical scan of LegalWorkspace for forks, inline fetch, cross-package imports</tool>
    <tool name="read">Inspect re-export files for shape</tool>
  </tools>

